what to check before making a distribution/release
(check version numbers)

check
 - ChangeLog
 - README win/README_windows.txt
 - pdfdoc (requirements, etc)


Version numbers

in pdfdoc
 * jpg/logo.jpg
 * GPLIGC_Manual.tex
 then =>  sh compileit.sh

in /
 * configure.ac
 * ChangeLog
 then => autoreconf -iv

in perl
 * GPLIGC.pl


=> ./configure ; make distcheck
=> webinstall-scripts on pc12...

TEST the release tarball

=> git commit, git -s tag VERSION (vX.Y)

clean-up: (this should clean up everything down to the tracked files)
=> sh cleaner.sh

WINDOWS:
cygwin (svn update),  in pdfdoc sh copyfrompc12
mingw, in win VERSION=xx.y ./makedist

